hopobject.body: Enter your PIN leanmode walmart Millennial’s not the only network that’s struggling to turn a profit. Jumptap was recently sold to Millennial, seemingly in the hope that the scale of their combined businesses will help turn things around for both of them. Meanwhile, Velti, which operates a mobile ad network and exchange, has seen its share price plummet as it lays off staff and burns through cash in order to stay afloat. There’s a whole host of private companies that are likely in a similar situation but refuse to disclose information about their financial performances.
